en_152107_0	The reconstruction of the Meda Oyamaduwa tank in Maha Vilachchiya commenced today under the patronage of Prime Minister Ranil Wickremasinghe.
en_152107_1	Development activities related to the Meda Oyamaduwa tank is being carried out under the Smart Irrigation Project mooted by the Ministry of Irrigation and Agriculture based on World Bank assistance.
en_152107_2	The estimated cost of this development work is five million rupees.
en_152107_3	It is planned to reconstruct the Meda Oyamaduwa tank bund, prepare the bunds and remove silt.
en_152107_4	A large number of farmer families in the area will benefit.
en_152107_5	Members of the Maha Sangha including Chief Incumbent of the Atamasthana the Ven.
en_152107_6	Pallegama Sirinivasa Thera and many Parliamentarians were present.
